claim.claim-text:
1. A device comprising:
a hardware processor to:
transmit an authentication request to a first server prior to transmitting a request for a resource to a second server, the first server being a policy server;
receive, based on the transmitted authentication request, an authentication response from the first server indicating authentication of the device to the first server;
transmit a request for the resource to the second server;
receive, from the second server and based on the transmitted request for the resource, a redirection signal that includes a request for verification of the device; and
transmit the redirection signal to the first server for verification;
receive, from the first server, one or more commands based on transmitting the redirection signal;
receive, from the first server, a plug-in;
use the received one or more commands and the received plug-in to identify a session associated with the device;
receive, from the first server, a verification message based on the identified session;
transmit the verification message to the second server;
cause the session to be established; and
receive, based on causing the session to be established, the requested resource from the second server after the verification message is transmitted to the second server.

8. A non-transitory computer-readable medium storing instructions, the instructions comprising:
one or more instructions which, when executed by at least one processor, cause the at least one processor to transmit authentication information to a first server prior to transmitting a request for a resource to a second server, the first server being a policy server;
one or more instructions which, when executed by the at least one processor, cause the at least one processor to receive an authentication response from the first server;
one or more instructions which, when executed by the at least one processor, cause the at least one processor to authenticate a device based on receiving the authentication response, the device including an agent;
one or more instructions which, when executed by the at least one processor, cause the at least one processor to transmit the request for the resource to the second server;
one or more instructions which, when executed by the at least one processor, cause the at least one processor to receive a request from the second server to verify the authenticity of the device;
one or more instructions which, when executed by the at least one processor, cause the at least one processor to transmit the request from the second server to the first server;
one or more instructions which, when executed by the at least one processor, cause the at least one processor to receive, from the first server, a plug-in;
one or more instructions which, when executed by the at least one processor, cause the at least one processor to communicate with the agent for verifying the authenticity of the device;
one or more instructions which, when executed by the at least one processor, cause the at least one processor to receive a message from the agent verifying the authenticity of the device;
one or more instructions which, when executed by the at least one processor, cause the at least one processor to transmit information verifying the authenticity of the device to the first server;
one or more instructions which, when executed by the at least one processor, cause the at least one processor to receive a verification message, based on the transmitted information verifying the authenticity of the device, from the first server,
the verification message being received after the plug-in;

one or more instructions which, when executed by the at least one processor, cause the at least one processor to send the verification message to the second server to authenticate the device to the second server;
one or more instructions which, when executed by the at least one processor, cause the at least one processor to establish a session with the agent; and
one or more instructions which, when executed by the at least one processor, cause the at least one processor to receive, based on establishing the session, the requested resource from the second server.

14. A method implemented by a device, the method comprising:
transmitting, by the device and prior to transmitting a request for a resource to a second server, an authentication request to a first server, the first server being a policy server;
receiving, by the device and based on the transmitted authentication request, an authentication response from the first server;
transmitting, by the device, the request for the resource to the second server;
receiving, by the device and from the second server based on the transmitted request for the resource, a redirection signal that includes a request for verification of the device, the redirection signal being intended for the first server;
transmitting, by the device, the redirection signal to the first server;
receiving, by the device and from the first server, instructions based on transmitting the redirection signal;
receiving, by the device and from the first server, a plug-in;
using, by the device, the received instructions and the received plug-in to identify a session associated with the device;
receiving, by the device and from the first server, a verification message based on the identified session;
transmitting, by the device, the verification message to the second server;
establishing, by the device, the session; and
receiving, by the device and based on establishing the session, the requested resource from the second server.
